{"lemma":"وَحْشِ","slug":"وَحْشِ","root":"#.ح.ش","root_slug":"_-ح-ش","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ح-ش","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1341","n1342","n1343","n41751","","n41756","n41757"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%88%D9%8E%D8%AD%D9%92%D8%B4%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wild animal"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"monster"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"beast","examples":[{"text":"إِذَا ٱلشَّمْسُ كُوِّرَتْ (1) وَإِذَا ٱلنُّجُومُ ٱنْكَدَرَتْ (2) وَإِذَا ٱلْجِبَالُ سُيِّرَتْ (3) وَإِذَا ٱلْعِشَارُ عُطِّلَتْ (4) وَإِذَا ٱلْوُحُوشُ حُشِرَتْ (5) وَإِذَا ٱلْبِحَارُ سُجِّرَتْ (6) وَإِذَا ٱلنُّفُوسُ زُوِّجَتْ (7) وَإِذَا ٱلْمَوْءُودَةُ سُئِلَتْ (8) بِأَيِّ ذَنْبٍ قُتِلَتْ (9) وَإِذَا ٱلصُّحُفُ نُشِرَتْ (10) وَإِذَا ٱلسَّمَاءُ كُشِطَتْ (11) وَإِذَا ٱلْجَحِيمُ سُعِّرَتْ (12) وَإِذَا ٱلْجَنَّةُ أُزْلِفَتْ (13) عَلِمَتْ نَفْسٌ مَا أَحْضَرَتْ (14)"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"game"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to throw away (clothes, arms, etc) [+بِ (object)] while fleeing"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to abound with wild beasts"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fall into poverty or contempt, grow savage and brute-like, be devastated and unpeopled"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to feel lonely or miss"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1341","headword_ar":"وحش","root":"Ans","body":[{"kind":"text","text":":) [and the like is said, as a citation from Az, in the Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wH$","text_ar":"وحش"},{"kind":"text","text":": but after this, in my copy of the Msb, there seems to be an omission; for it is immediately added, “But Az says, This is not correct in my opinion:”] it is said that everything that is frightened declines to its right side; for the beast is approached to be mounted and milked on the left side, and, fearing thereat, runs away from the place of fear, which is the left side, to the place of safety, which is the right side: (S, * IAmb in Msb; both in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wH$","text_ar":"وحش"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [accordingly,] Er-Rá'ee describes a beast as declining to the side termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwH$Y","text_ar":"الوحشى"},{"kind":"text","text":"because frightened on the left side: (S and Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wH$","text_ar":"وحش"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and 'Antarah alludes to one's shrinking with the side so termed from the whip, [which he likens to a cat,] because the whip of the rider is in his right hand: (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wH$","text_ar":"وحش"},{"kind":"text","text":":) but Abu-l-'Abbás says that people differ respecting these two terms when relating to a man: that, accord. to some, they mean the same in this case as in the cases of horses"},{"kind":"page_break","n":115},{"kind":"text","text":"and other beasts of carriage, and of camels: but some say, that in the case of a man, the latter term means the part next the shoulder-blade; and the former, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part next the arm-pit."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n1342","headword_ar":"وحش","root":"Ans","body":[{"kind":"text","text":".) Of every double member of a man, as the upper half of each arm, and the two fore arms, and the two feet, it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That"},{"kind":"text","text":"[side]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is towards the man;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wH$Y~","text_ar":"وحشىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", that which turns away from him: (As, S:) or, of the foot, the former means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that"},{"kind":"text","text":"[side]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is towards the other foot;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e., the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inner"},{"kind":"text","text":"side;] and the latter, the contrary of the former. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wH$","text_ar":"وحش"},{"kind":"text","text":".) Of a bow, (S, M, K,) or of a Persian bow, (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wH$","text_ar":"وحش"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That"},{"kind":"text","text":"[side]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is towards thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wH$Y~","text_ar":"وحشىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the back: (S and K in art."}],"source_refs":["As","S","M","K"]},{"entry_id":"n1343","headword_ar":"وحش","root":"Ans","body":[{"kind":"text","text":":) or the former,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that"},{"kind":"text","text":"[side]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is next to the archer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter, that which is next to the animal shot at: (M, TA:) or of a bow, whether Persian or not is not said, [the former means the side"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against which the arrow lies;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and] the latter, the side against which the arrow does not lie. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wH$","text_ar":"وحش"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anasiY~N","text_ar":"اَنَسِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosN","text_ar":"اـِنْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosiY~N","text_ar":"اـِنْسِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", each in two places."}],"source_refs":["M","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n41751","headword_ar":"وَحُشَ","root":"wH$","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", [inf. n., probably,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuHuw$apN","text_ar":"وُحُوشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHaA$apN","text_ar":"وَحَاشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or both,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a place)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abounded with wild animals."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKtt.) [The meaning assigned to this verb in Freytag's Lex. belongs not to it, but to"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2929},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waxu$a","text_ar":"وَخُشَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHa$a bihi","text_ar":"وَحَشَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihaA","text_ar":"بِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":",] aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaHi$u","text_ar":"يَحِشُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHo$N","text_ar":"وَحْشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TK;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wH~$","text_ar":"وحّش","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihaA","text_ar":"بِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A,) which latter form of the verb is disapproved by IAar, but both are correct; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"twH~$","text_ar":"توحّش","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. used alone, the objective complement being understood]; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He threw it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"them, away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a distance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,) namely, his garment, (S, K,) or his garments, (A,) and his sword, (TA,) and his spear, (S, TA,) and his weapon, or weapons, (S, A,) or anything, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to lighten himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his beast of carriage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in fear of his being overtaken:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in any case;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] it is said in a trad. of El-Ows and ElKhazraj,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawaHa$uwA biA^asoliHatihimo wA@Eotanaqa baEoDuhumo baEoDFA","text_ar":"فَوَحَشُوا بِاَسْلِحَتِهِمْ وا@عْتَنَقَ بَعْضُهُمْ بَعْضًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Then they threw away their weapons, and embraced one another"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["IAar","K","S","A","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n41756","headword_ar":"وَحْشٌ","root":"wH$","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a country, or region, (S, K,) and a place, (TA,) and a house ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dAarN","text_ar":"داَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (A,) and [its fem.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHo$apN","text_ar":"وَحْشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a land ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (S, TA,) to a house ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dAr","text_ar":"دار"},{"kind":"text","text":"); (A;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Desolate, deserted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destitute of human beings"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inhabitants;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muwHi$N","text_ar":"مُوحِشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutawaH~i$N","text_ar":"مُتَوَحِّشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN waHo$apN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ وَحْشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musotawoHi$apN","text_ar":"مُسْتَوْحِشَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same. (K, TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bilaAdN Hi$uwna","text_ar":"بِلَادٌ حِشُونَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Countries,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"regions, desolate, deserted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; after the manner of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sinuwna","text_ar":"سِنُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in the accus. and gen.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hi$iyna","text_ar":"حِشِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl., as Az says, of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hi$apN","text_ar":"حِشَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHo$N","text_ar":"وَحْشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [So I read instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHo$ap","text_ar":"وَحْشَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is evidently a mistranscription,] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"being wanting, as it is in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zinapN","text_ar":"زِنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SilapN","text_ar":"صِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EidapN","text_ar":"عِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You also say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiytuhu biwaHo$i A_iSomita","text_ar":"لَقِيتُهُ بِوَحْشِ اـِصْمِتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iSomitapa","text_ar":"اـِصْمِتَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I found him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"met him, in a desolate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deserted, country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"region."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) [See remarks on the last word in the former phrase in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Smt","text_ar":"صمت"},{"kind":"text","text":".] And in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarakotuhu biwaHo$i Almatoni","text_ar":"تَرَكْتُهُ بِوَحْشِ المَتْنِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I left him in the desert part of the elevated plain, where one could not reach him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA. *) And [hence]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HimaAru","text_ar":"حِمَارُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHo$K","text_ar":"وَحْشٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An ass of a desert;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wild ass;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HimaArN waHo$iY~N","text_ar":"حِمَارٌ وَحْشِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqaru AlwaHo$i","text_ar":"بَقَرُ الوَحْشِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bull and cow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bulls and cows,"},{"kind":"text","text":"collectively,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the desert;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the wild bull and cow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bulls and cows."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-  [Hence also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Animals"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayawaAn","text_ar":"حَيَوَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is used as a sing. and a pl., but is here meant to be understood collectively, as appears from what follows,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the desert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as are not tame;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild animals;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of the fem. gender; (TA;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuHuw$N","text_ar":"وُحُوشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHiy$N","text_ar":"وَحِيشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) these three words are all used in a collective sense: (ISh:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHo$iY~N","text_ar":"وَحْشِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single one of such animals;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zanojiY~N","text_ar":"زَنْجِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in relation to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zanojN","text_ar":"زَنْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruwmiY~N","text_ar":"رُومِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruwmN","text_ar":"رُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHo$N","text_ar":"وَحْشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is not tame, of beasts of the desert;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"everything that is afraid of human beings"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~u $aYo'K yasotawoHi$u","text_ar":"كُلُّ شَىْءٍ يَسْتَوْحِشُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eani Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"عَنِ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"); as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHo$iY~N","text_ar":"وَحْشِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as though the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"were a corroborative, as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dw~aAriY~N","text_ar":"دوَّارِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or, accord. to El-Fárábee,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHo$N","text_ar":"وَحْشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the pl. [lexicologically, but not in the language of the grammarians] of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHo$iY~N","text_ar":"وَحْشِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruwmN","text_ar":"رُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruwmiY~N","text_ar":"رُومِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or it is used as a sing., as well as collectively; for you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA waHo$N DaxomN","text_ar":"هٰذَا وَحْشٌ ضَخْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this is a bulky wild animal"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi $aApN waHo$N","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ شَاةٌ وَحْشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this is a wild sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (ISh:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuHuw$N","text_ar":"وُحُوشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHo$N","text_ar":"وَحْشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) and so is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuHo$aAnN","text_ar":"وُحْشَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sgh, K,) and so is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHiy$N","text_ar":"وَحِيشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [lexicologically, but grammarians term it a quasi-pl. n.,] like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Day^iynN","text_ar":"ضَيِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaA^onN","text_ar":"ضَاْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sgh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuHuw$N","text_ar":"وُحُوشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is its only broken pl. (TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wild,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to girls or women: see an ex. of the word in this sense voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taw~N","text_ar":"تَوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", where it has a redundant"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"affixed to it.] ―         -b4-  [Hence also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lone; solitary; without company."},{"kind":"text","text":"You say."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aY fiY AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"مَشَى فِى الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHo$FA","text_ar":"وَحْشًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He walked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went, in the land alone, having no other with him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  [Hence also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hungry;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muwHi$N","text_ar":"مُوحِشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, A,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutawaH~i$N","text_ar":"مُتَوَحِّشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHi$N","text_ar":"وَحِشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl. of the first,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awoHaA$N","text_ar":"اَوْحَاشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHo$uwna","text_ar":"وَحْشُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAta fulaAnN waHo$FA","text_ar":"بَاتَ فُلَانٌ وَحْشًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, * K, *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muwHi$FA","text_ar":"مُوحِشًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutawaH~i$FA","text_ar":"مُتَوَحِّشًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one passed the night hungry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not having eaten anything, so that his inside was empty."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bitonaA waHo$iyna","text_ar":"بِتْنَا وَحْشِينَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We passed the night without food."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [In another place in the TA, we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqado bitonaA layolatanaA h`*ihi waHo$iY","text_ar":"لَقَدْ بِتْنَا لَيْلَتَنَا هٰذِهِ وَحْشِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and so in the L; the last word being evidently a mistranscription, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHo$iyna","text_ar":"وَحْشِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and it is added, as though the speaker meant,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamaAEapa waHo$aY","text_ar":"جَمَاعَةَ وَحْشَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; doubtless a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamaAEapa waHo$K","text_ar":"جَمَاعَةَ وَحْشٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"so that the saying seems to mean,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We have passed this our night"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a company of wild animals."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","A","ISh","Msb","Sgh","AZ"]},{"entry_id":"n41757","headword_ar":"وَحِشٌ","root":"wH$","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHo$N","text_ar":"وَحْشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last signification."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}